Atlas, Banco de Oro, Manila Electric: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-06-27T23:45:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/atlas-banco-de-oro-manila-electric-philippine-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and share prices are as of the most recent
trading day.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 2.15, or 0.1
percent, to 4,289.29 at the noon close in  Manila .  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp: The
Philippine miner expects to reach a deal with a potential
investor within the week, Chairman Alfredo Ramos told reporters
in Manila yesterday. Ramos said he hasn’t met Philex Mining
Corp. Chairman Manuel Pangilinan or any of its officials.  Atlas may need $200 million to fund a planned output
expansion to 100,000 tons per day, Vice President Adrian Ramos
told reporters. Atlas’ unit Carmen Copper Corp. currently
produces about 40,000 tons per day of mostly copper
concentrates. The stock rose 5.4 percent to 20 pesos on June 23
before it was suspended.  Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO)  : The nation’s largest
lender by assets sold 8.5 billion pesos ($195 million) of notes
to boost capital. The notes, which were priced at 6.5 percent
per year, have a maturity of 10 years and three months, and a
 call option  after five years, it said in a regulatory filing
yesterday. The stock was unchanged at 54.90 pesos.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  : The country’s largest power
retailer said a unit will invest in a venture that will build a
600-megawatt coal-fired power plant in Zambales province.
Meralco PowerGen Corp. will take a majority stake in Redondo
Peninsula Energy Inc, which is owned by  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)   unit Therma Power Inc. and Taiwan Cogeneration Corp.
Manila Electric rose 1.6 percent to 275 pesos. Aboitiz Power
gained 0.5 percent to 30.60 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
